property.name: problemSolution
property.value:
The MATLAB script gives the following output:

 

>> A = [1:3;2:2:6;3:-1:1]

 

A =

     1     2     3
     2     4     6
     3     2     1

 

>> A = A'

 

A =

     1     2     3
     2     4     2
     3     6     1

 

>> A(:,3) = []

 

A =

     1     2
     2     4
     3     6

 

>> A = [A(:,1) [4 5 7]' A(:,2)]

 

A =

     1     4     2
     2     5     4
     3     7     6

 

>> A = sum(diag(A))

 

A =

    12

sectionBreak.stem:
The MATLAB humps function defines a curve that has 2 maxima (peaks) of unequal height over the interval 0 ≤ x ≤ 2:

 

%media:formula4.mml%

 

Use MATLAB to generate a plot of f (x) versus x with

 

x = [0:1/256:2];

 

Do not use MATLAB’s built-in humps function to generate the values of f (x). Also, employ the minimum number of periods to perform the vector operations needed to generate f (x) values for the plot.

internal_category.title: ABET Outcomes: (a) an ability to apply knowledge of mathematics, science, and engineering

property.name: problemSolution
property.value:
The MATLAB script to generate the plot is

 

clc,clf,format compact
x=[0:1/256:2];
y=1./((x-0.3).^2+0.01)+1./((x-0.9)^2+0.04)-6;
plot(x,y)

hint.name: hint #1
hint.value: Recall the uses of period operator.
